         <abstract id="aspace_b949d4dfc8c36dca4c32f41ea9c409dc">Correspondence to family members and others, dating from 1919 to 1961, provides detailed documentation of Isely's life and work in Turkey. Merrill Isely and his wife Mildred were missionaries serving under the American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions in Gaziantep, Turkey for four decades beginning in 1920.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname source="local">
               <part>Isely, Merrill N.</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
